            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains a range of publications compiled or distributed by John J. Flinn (1851-1929) for the World&#039;s Columbian Exposition in Chicago.</p>
                                 <p>Included are copies of the <emph render="italic">Official Guide to the World&#039;s Columbian Exposition</emph> (Authorized, Hand Book, and Souvenir editions), the <emph render="italic">Hand-Book of the World&#039;s Columbian Exposition</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Best Things to be Seen at the World&#039;s Fair</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Buildings of the World&#039;s Fair</emph>, and the <emph render="italic">Complete Guide to Chicago and the World&#039;s Fair. </emph>In all, Flinn&#039;s Standard Guide Company advertised nine guides, and also printed pamphlets about the Fair with covers that advertised nearby hotels.</p>
                                 <p>The collection also includes a set of Charles S. Graham&#039;s color prints of scenes of the Fair, certificates, and a mock-up of Flinn&#039;s <emph render="italic">Chicago Hand-Book of Biography</emph> (1893).</p>
                                 <p>John J. Roche, Flinn&#039;s grandson, donated the collection to the Library in 1995.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


